# Repository Structure

**Project**: WebRTC Engineering (personal learning workspace)

> **Single Source of Truth**: For the complete and detailed repository structure, naming conventions, and workflow standards, refer to [docs/01-repository-structure.md](../../docs/01-repository-structure.md).

## Quick Summary

- **`src/NN-category/topic-name/`**: Topic modules grouped by learning area (fundamentals, signaling, networking, etc.).
- **Four layers per topic**: `01-notes/`, `02-exercises/`, `03-implementations/`, `04-discussions/`.
- **`docs/`**: Architecture notes, RFC summaries, diagrams, agent docs, and reviews.
- **`experiments/`**: Bandwidth, codec, and load-testing experiments.
- **`assets/`**: Images, diagrams, and media assets.
- **`tools/`**: Maintenance scripts (`pyscripts/`, `psscripts/`).

When writing or updating public-facing structure (for example `README.md` or `docs/01-repository-structure.md`), do not list or mention any internal-only paths.

## Preserved archives

- `.archive/` contains old category-based learning content. Leave it as preserved legacy material unless Swamy explicitly asks to migrate or clean it.
- Routine parity, docs, and CI reviews should focus on active `src/` topic modules and governance/tooling consistency.
